  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "Who are the best angel investors of all time?",
  "response": "The concept of \"best\" can be subjective and depends on various factors such as the success of their investments, their influence on the startup ecosystem, and their overall impact on the companies they invest in. That being said, here are some of the most notable and influential angel investors of all time:\n\n1. **Ron Conway**\n   - Known as the \"Godfather of Silicon Valley,\" Ron Conway has invested in numerous successful startups including Google, Facebook, Twitter, and Airbnb. He is renowned for his early-stage investments and extensive network.\n\n2. **Peter Thiel**\n   - Co-founder of PayPal and an early investor in Facebook, Peter Thiel is one of the most influential angel investors. His $500,000 investment in Facebook turned into more than $1 billion, showcasing his keen eye for potential.\n\n3. **Chris Sacca**\n   - Through his venture fund Lowercase Capital, Chris Sacca has made successful investments in companies like Twitter, Uber, and Instagram. His early investments have often resulted in substantial returns.\n\n4. **Reid Hoffman**\n   - As the co-founder of LinkedIn, Reid Hoffman has been an active angel investor in numerous successful startups including Facebook, Airbnb, and Dropbox. His strategic investments and mentorship have been highly valuable to entrepreneurs.\n\n5. **Naval Ravikant**\n   - Co-founder of AngelList, Naval Ravikant has played a significant role in democratizing startup investing. He has invested in companies like Uber, Twitter, and Postmates, leveraging his insights into technology and business.\n\n6. **Jason Calacanis**\n   - Known for his early investments in Uber and Thumbtack, Jason Calacanis has a knack for identifying promising startups. His podcast and newsletter have also made him a notable figure in the startup community.\n\n7. **Esther Dyson**\n   - A long-time technology investor and commentator, Esther Dyson has made early investments in companies like Flickr and Square. Her insights into the tech industry have been widely respected.\n\n8. **Aydin Senkut**\n   - Founder of Felicis Ventures, Aydin Senkut has invested in companies like Fitbit, Shopify, and Meraki. His firm has been known for its early-stage investments that often lead to significant exits.\n\n9. **Fabrice Grinda**\n   - With a diverse portfolio of over 200 companies, Fabrice Grinda has had successful exits with companies like Alibaba, Lending Club, and Fanatics. His global approach to angel investing is noteworthy.\n\n10. **Jeff Clavier**\n    - Founder of SoftTech VC, Jeff Clavier has made impactful investments in companies like Mint, Wildfire, and Postmates. His focus on software and internet startups has led to numerous successful exits.\n\nThese investors not only provide capital but also mentorship, strategic advice, and access to valuable networks, which are critical for the success of startups. Their influence extends beyond their financial contributions, making them some of the best angel investors of all time.",
